This README file contains information on the contents of the
openfest layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/bitbake
  branch: master

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
  layers: meta
  branch: master

Patches
=======

Please submit any patches with pull requests to:
https://github.com/leon-anavi/meta-openfest

Maintainer: Leon Anavi <leon@anavi.org>


Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the openfest layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the openfest layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the openfest layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the openfest layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-openfest \
    "


